race.comment: The feature of the day now and it looks to shape well for SILVER EYE (2). He flew home in a 78+ at Ascot last time out when getting well back from the wide draw, but did just miss in the same grade two back when sitting closer. The inside draw should see him get every chance and with some rivals drawn awkwardly, he can capitalise. THE CALABRESE (14) flew home to win in Saturday grade last time out and did so in easy fashion. He's likely to be back from the draw once again, but he's on the way up and can improve again third-up into the campaign. He looks the main danger. THEHORSEMAN (7) went to Ascot last start after winning three on-end here to begin the campaign. He maps for a lovely run under ZJP and he's no doubt been set for this on his home deck. Plenty to lie. SUPERSESSION (3) has trialled well between runs and gets the blinkers back on today with Faithfull riding. Plenty to like. JUST SAINT JAMES (6) can build on the first-up win.
